WEBVTT

00:01.150 --> 00:03.002
<i> Previously</i>
<i> on "women of the movement"...</i>

00:03.120 --> 00:05.037
Let bobo come on down there
with us.

00:05.122 --> 00:06.872
Mississippi is not
like chicago.

00:06.974 --> 00:08.507
I know.
No, you don't.

00:08.626 --> 00:10.426
Mamie:
When you're down there and
a white person approaches you,

00:10.511 --> 00:11.660
what do you do?

00:11.762 --> 00:13.762
I keep my eyes down.
You keep
your whole head down.

00:13.848 --> 00:15.381
You kneel on the street
if you have to.

00:15.466 --> 00:18.767
[ wolf-whistle ]
maurice: Boy, are you crazy?

00:18.853 --> 00:21.053
Word gets out
that we let this go,

00:21.138 --> 00:22.604
it is not gonna stop
with talking.

00:22.690 --> 00:24.773
The hell you expect me
to do?
Find him.

00:24.859 --> 00:26.358
Lizzie: Please, lord!
Don't take him, please!

00:26.477 --> 00:27.726
Uncle mose:
No need to carry him off.

00:27.812 --> 00:29.028
He ain't but 14!

00:29.146 --> 00:31.530
Ollie: They think
they found emmett -- his body.

00:31.649 --> 00:32.898
Dr. Otken:
I've never seen such damage

00:32.983 --> 00:34.616
in such a short amount of time.

00:34.702 --> 00:36.735
I honestly don't see any use
for an autopsy.

00:36.821 --> 00:38.821
That's it, then.
We'll be taking it from here.

00:38.906 --> 00:40.656
The boy was abducted
in leflore county.

00:40.741 --> 00:41.990
That's our jurisdiction.

00:42.076 --> 00:43.692
We found him 10 miles
into tallahatchie county.

00:43.794 --> 00:44.993
You're on my turf.

00:45.079 --> 00:47.913
Ain't no one gonna ship
that body out of mississippi.

00:47.998 --> 00:49.298
You get it in the ground.

00:49.383 --> 00:50.799
They're trying
to cover it up.

00:50.885 --> 00:52.584
I have contacts
in mississippi.

00:52.686 --> 00:56.088
I'll see if he can help us
get your son home.

00:56.173 --> 00:58.841
Mamie: People need to know.
I want a public wake.

00:58.926 --> 00:59.892
Tonight.

01:00.010 --> 01:01.209
Open casket.

01:01.312 --> 01:03.629
And I don't want you doing
a thing to him.

01:04.397 --> 01:06.765
Guide:<i> That beautiful</i>
<i> colonial mansion over there</i>

01:06.851 --> 01:08.267
<i> is mr. Alan ladd's home.</i>

01:08.352 --> 01:09.902
<i> Alan ladd!</i>

01:10.020 --> 01:11.437
<i> Yeah, gee, it would be nice</i>
<i> if we could see</i>

01:11.522 --> 01:13.238
<i> sue carol walking</i>
<i> around there.</i>

01:13.357 --> 01:15.891
<i> And over here on the left</i>
<i> is shirley temp--</i>

01:15.943 --> 01:19.144
<i> this is a wduw chicago</i>
<i> special bulletin.</i>

01:19.213 --> 01:22.214
<i> The body identified</i>
<i> as 14-year-old emmett till</i>

01:22.283 --> 01:25.000
<i> arrived by train this morning.</i>

01:25.052 --> 01:27.453
<i> Till's mother, mamie bradley,</i>
<i> met the train</i>

01:27.521 --> 01:29.655
<i> at the central street station</i>
<i> this morning</i>

01:29.723 --> 01:32.291
<i>and has since made a statement,</i>
<i> inviting the public.</i>

01:32.359 --> 01:33.459
<i> The viewing will be held</i>

01:33.494 --> 01:35.027
<i> at a.A. Rayner & sons</i>
<i> funeral home...</i>

01:35.096 --> 01:36.111
The hell is this?

01:36.163 --> 01:37.179
<i> All those wishing to pay --</i>
[ click ]

01:37.231 --> 01:46.371
♪♪

01:46.474 --> 01:55.647
♪♪

01:55.716 --> 01:59.685
I know you asked me
to leave him be.

01:59.753 --> 02:01.453
But...

02:01.522 --> 02:04.323
There's a whole lot
of people outside

02:04.391 --> 02:08.660
waiting to pay
their respects.

02:08.762 --> 02:10.829
And I just...

02:10.931 --> 02:14.032
Well --

02:14.068 --> 02:19.905
I felt I had to do<i> something</i>
to make it easier on them.

02:20.007 --> 02:23.709
♪♪

02:23.777 --> 02:27.129
it's just a-a few stitches.

02:30.651 --> 02:33.085
I hope that's okay.

02:33.154 --> 02:36.121
♪♪

02:36.190 --> 02:40.275
you did a beautiful job,
mr. Rayner.

02:40.361 --> 02:45.197
♪♪

02:45.299 --> 02:50.202
♪♪

02:50.304 --> 02:54.173
we don't have to open
the doors.

02:54.241 --> 02:57.142
Your family's here.
We can keep it private.

02:57.244 --> 03:00.379
No one else has to see.

03:00.447 --> 03:05.450
I want them to see...
What was taken from me.

03:05.553 --> 03:12.758
♪♪

03:12.826 --> 03:20.115
♪♪

03:20.167 --> 03:27.372
♪♪

03:27.441 --> 03:30.309
let them in.

03:30.411 --> 03:39.017
♪♪

03:39.119 --> 03:41.470
[ door opens ]

03:41.555 --> 03:47.859
♪♪

03:47.928 --> 03:54.283
♪♪

03:54.335 --> 03:55.968
[ indistinct conversations ]

03:56.070 --> 04:02.741
♪♪

04:02.843 --> 04:09.514
♪♪

04:09.600 --> 04:10.649
[ both crying ]

04:10.734 --> 04:12.718
no!

04:12.836 --> 04:15.070
[ sobbing ]

04:15.105 --> 04:18.390
♪♪

04:26.566 --> 04:28.700
<i> reports estimate that</i>
<i> more than 10,000 people</i>

04:28.786 --> 04:30.335
<i> have already viewed</i>
<i> emmett till's body,</i>

04:30.454 --> 04:32.587
<i> with that number sure to climb</i>
<i> today at the funer--</i>

04:32.673 --> 04:34.823
[ click ]

04:34.925 --> 04:37.542
who do you think we feeding,
an army?

04:37.628 --> 04:39.261
The same people
we've been feeding

04:39.346 --> 04:41.997
since this nightmare began.

04:42.099 --> 04:44.016
The repast
is for family.

04:44.134 --> 04:45.801
I don't know why you
feel the need

04:45.886 --> 04:49.054
to feed the entire chicago
branch of the naacp.

04:49.156 --> 04:50.639
After everything
they've done for emmett,

04:50.724 --> 04:52.674
they might as well
be family.

04:52.776 --> 04:55.610
Folks are gonna be expecting
a meal after the funeral,

04:55.696 --> 05:00.032
and I'd rather have too much
than not enough.

05:00.150 --> 05:01.850
We need time
to grieve.

05:01.952 --> 05:04.119
I'm not standing
in your way, mama.

05:05.990 --> 05:09.908
<i> You</i> need time
to grieve.

05:09.994 --> 05:12.744
I will.

05:12.830 --> 05:14.863
When those monsters are indicted
by a grand jury

05:14.965 --> 05:17.883
and when they're in prison
for the rest of their lives.

05:18.002 --> 05:20.252
And what if it doesn't go
our way?

05:20.337 --> 05:21.420
Mama, don't.

05:21.505 --> 05:24.372
An arrest [chuckles]
was a miracle,

05:24.475 --> 05:27.676
but an indictment --

05:27.761 --> 05:31.046
that doesn't happen.
Not for us.

05:31.148 --> 05:33.348
I'm sorry.

05:33.434 --> 05:36.902
But it needed to
be said.

05:37.021 --> 05:39.054
Now, you know I don't keep
my good containers

05:39.156 --> 05:40.238
on that bottom shelf.

05:40.357 --> 05:41.406
Go on.

05:41.525 --> 05:42.741
Car's on the way,
so we best get ready

05:42.860 --> 05:43.775
if we don't want to be late.

05:43.861 --> 05:44.943
Tell 'em to wait.

05:45.029 --> 05:48.030
As if they'd start
the funeral without us.

05:48.115 --> 05:50.365
You know what?

05:50.451 --> 05:52.951
In this case,
maybe they would.

06:01.128 --> 06:02.077
Some people are better

06:02.179 --> 06:04.463
at putting on a brave face
than others,

06:04.548 --> 06:08.383
but if you get tired
of putting yours on today,

06:08.469 --> 06:09.885
you let me know.

06:12.356 --> 06:13.972
I'll sneak you out
the church's back door.

06:14.058 --> 06:17.142
[ chuckles softly ]
I'm fine.

06:17.227 --> 06:18.310
I will be,

06:18.395 --> 06:20.645
as long as I don't
sit still for too long.

06:20.731 --> 06:22.564
Just say the word.

06:22.649 --> 06:25.751
[ organ playing ]

06:25.853 --> 06:31.272
♪♪

06:31.375 --> 06:33.375
♪ I don't know why ♪

06:33.460 --> 06:37.112
♪ I don't know why ♪

06:37.214 --> 06:43.268
♪ I have to cry sometimes ♪

06:43.370 --> 06:45.087
♪ I don't know why ♪

06:45.172 --> 06:49.391
♪ I don't know why ♪

06:49.476 --> 06:56.348
♪ I have to sigh, ooh,
sometimes ♪

06:56.433 --> 07:01.803
♪ it would be a perfect day ♪

07:01.905 --> 07:04.639
♪ but there's trouble ♪

07:04.741 --> 07:07.192
♪ in my way ♪

07:07.277 --> 07:10.662
♪ I don't know why ♪

07:10.781 --> 07:13.165
♪ but I'll find out ♪
[ sobs ]

07:13.283 --> 07:16.484
♪ by and by ♪

07:16.587 --> 07:19.037
♪ ooh, it would be a ♪

07:19.123 --> 07:22.424
♪ be a perfect day ♪

07:22.509 --> 07:27.679
♪ but my trouble
keep on getting in the way ♪

07:27.798 --> 07:31.133
♪ I don't know why ♪

07:31.218 --> 07:34.302
♪ but I'll find out ♪

07:34.388 --> 07:39.340
♪ lord ♪

07:39.443 --> 07:43.528
♪ by and by ♪

07:43.647 --> 07:45.647
remember.

07:45.732 --> 07:47.115
Just say the word.

07:47.201 --> 07:50.368
♪♪

07:50.487 --> 07:51.870
bishop:
Good morning.

07:51.989 --> 07:53.288
Congregation:
Good morning.

07:53.373 --> 07:56.541
To the members
of emmett's family

07:56.660 --> 07:59.845
and, first and foremost,
to his mother,

07:59.930 --> 08:02.447
let me begin by saying
that this community

08:02.533 --> 08:04.933
is not only praying for you,

08:04.985 --> 08:08.720
but we are standing
<i> with</i> you.

08:09.940 --> 08:12.007
I would also like
to take this opportunity

08:12.042 --> 08:14.008
to thank local journalists

08:14.061 --> 08:17.195
for your thorough coverage
of this case.

08:17.264 --> 08:20.599
I pray that god blesses
each and every one of you

08:20.667 --> 08:22.133
for your fine work
that you've done

08:22.236 --> 08:25.070
to inform the citizens
of chicago

08:25.155 --> 08:28.940
and even the world
about this tragedy.

08:29.026 --> 08:32.394
[ congregation murmuring ]

08:32.429 --> 08:33.995
I have to be honest with you,
church.

08:34.031 --> 08:37.148
I-I had to wrestle with god

08:37.217 --> 08:38.783
about what I was gonna say
today.

08:38.852 --> 08:45.423
I...I know I should talk about
his love and peace,

08:45.459 --> 08:49.461
but this is a reckoning moment
in america.

08:49.546 --> 08:51.212
We are in pain!

08:51.265 --> 08:53.081
[ congregation murmuring ]

08:53.116 --> 08:56.401
but we can mourn later.

08:56.470 --> 09:00.639
For right now, we must act
on behalf of this young martyr,

09:00.707 --> 09:05.477
who was a casualty of the war
of good versus evil.

09:05.512 --> 09:08.446
And we must show that
the hatred of the creation

09:08.532 --> 09:12.200
cannot undo the love
and the power of the creator.

09:12.236 --> 09:13.401
[ congregation murmuring ]

09:13.453 --> 09:15.887
[ cash register clicks,
bell chimes ]

09:15.956 --> 09:17.505
[ music playing on radio ]

09:17.541 --> 09:20.525
alright.
Anything else, mr. Chatham?

09:20.611 --> 09:22.093
Well, I wouldn't mind
taking a few of them

09:22.162 --> 09:23.411
mary janes
off your hands.

09:23.497 --> 09:24.980
Sure.

09:25.065 --> 09:30.902
♪♪

09:30.988 --> 09:33.038
you know them?
Oh, no, sir.

09:33.106 --> 09:35.040
The way I figure it...
[ register clicks, ell chimes ]

09:35.125 --> 09:36.775
...We all gotta
stick together now.

09:36.860 --> 09:38.059
[ coins jingling ]

09:38.111 --> 09:40.862
anything you want to contribute
would be much appreciated.

09:40.897 --> 09:42.397
Not today, hon.

09:42.449 --> 09:46.851
♪♪

09:46.920 --> 09:49.237
I don't think so.
Oh.

09:49.339 --> 09:51.339
Jimmy hicks for
the<i> baltimore afro-american.</i>

09:51.391 --> 09:53.274
D.A. Chatham, what makes
this case different

09:53.327 --> 09:54.793
from the murder
of george lee in may

09:54.911 --> 09:56.511
or lamar smith
just weeks ago?

09:56.546 --> 09:59.464
We arrested two suspects
in the till case, that's what.

09:59.533 --> 10:01.900
Yeah, but how confident are you
in procuring indictments

10:01.935 --> 10:03.918
against the brothers
from an all-white grand jury?

10:03.954 --> 10:06.137
The state's gonna see that we
take every precaution

10:06.223 --> 10:07.889
to have a fair
and impartial jury.

10:07.975 --> 10:09.324
And you think that's possible
down here?

10:09.376 --> 10:11.426
I believe we have more
than sufficient evidence

10:11.445 --> 10:13.878
to convince 18 reasonable men
to render indictments

10:13.997 --> 10:16.298
when the grand jury convenes
on Monday morning.

10:16.383 --> 10:18.133
Y'all stay cool, now,
won't ya?

10:18.218 --> 10:19.918
Fittin' to be
a scorcher today.

10:29.146 --> 10:30.895
Strider: Can't hardly
walk down the street

10:31.014 --> 10:33.848
without some yank sticking
a microphone in your face.

10:33.934 --> 10:36.234
Well, I suppose
they're doing their jobs.

10:36.353 --> 10:39.604
Well, I wish they'd go do it
somewheres else.

10:40.440 --> 10:41.740
Until last night,

10:41.858 --> 10:45.443
I thought that body was buried
and in the ground.

10:45.529 --> 10:49.748
So you can imagine I was
a little, uh, miffed

10:49.866 --> 10:52.834
when I got word
it arrived in chicago.

10:52.919 --> 10:54.786
You don't think
the boy's mother had a right

10:54.871 --> 10:57.505
to dictate
where her son was buried?

10:57.591 --> 11:01.743
That wake, more like a tv show
than anything I'd ever seen.

11:01.845 --> 11:03.294
And from what I hear,

11:03.397 --> 11:06.581
that woman's back at it
again today with the funeral.

11:06.683 --> 11:08.800
Meanwhile, I got niggers
callin' the station,

11:08.885 --> 11:10.935
writing letters,
threatening to lynch me.

11:11.054 --> 11:13.688
You don't spook easy,
clarence.

11:13.774 --> 11:16.191
What's really eating
at you?

11:19.279 --> 11:21.696
Sheriff smith.

11:21.782 --> 11:24.449
He's poking his nose in
where it don't belong.

11:24.568 --> 11:26.768
The newspapers
published photographs

11:26.870 --> 11:30.205
of that cotton gin fan
that we found around the body,

11:30.290 --> 11:32.106
and I know he put 'em
up to it.

11:32.209 --> 11:35.210
He's only looking for
the gin fan's owner.

11:35.295 --> 11:36.944
Why can't he get it through
his thick skull?

11:37.047 --> 11:38.112
This case is mine.

11:38.215 --> 11:41.416
Because his kidnapping
investigation is ongoing,

11:41.501 --> 11:45.003
clarence, and if he can find out
where the gin fan came from,

11:45.088 --> 11:46.087
he'll have
a better idea

11:46.173 --> 11:47.972
of where the murder
actually took place,

11:48.091 --> 11:49.791
and then we'll all be
one step closer

11:49.893 --> 11:52.143
to locating witnesses
who can help track

11:52.262 --> 11:54.462
bryant and milam's movements
that night.

11:54.564 --> 11:55.447
Sheriff smith's
on our side.

11:55.565 --> 11:57.232
The hell he is!

11:57.317 --> 12:01.469
The gin fan is a piece
of evidence in my murder case.

12:01.571 --> 12:03.405
Always has been.

12:03.490 --> 12:07.575
Now, he knows damn well he's got
no right to get in my way.

12:07.661 --> 12:12.781
Now, gerald, I want you
to make it clear to him

12:12.866 --> 12:14.332
he's getting in<i> your</i> way
now, too.

12:14.451 --> 12:18.420
Oh, I'm not getting drawn into
some turf war between you two.

12:18.505 --> 12:21.423
Think of the press
like another tool in our belts

12:21.508 --> 12:23.875
to get
these indictments.

12:23.960 --> 12:27.662
You do realize that every
defense attorney in the county

12:27.764 --> 12:30.381
has stepped up for
milam and bryant, don't you?

12:30.467 --> 12:32.851
And I know how these cases
typically go,

12:32.969 --> 12:35.437
but this isn't
a typical case for us.

12:35.522 --> 12:38.389
We're talking about
a child.

12:38.492 --> 12:40.625
Folks don't go for that
down here.

12:40.727 --> 12:44.045
A whipping, maybe.

12:44.080 --> 12:45.463
But what they did
to that boy

12:45.565 --> 12:48.233
makes us all look
like a bunch of savages.

12:48.301 --> 12:51.152
And the papers are saying
10,000 people

12:51.188 --> 12:53.505
attended that boy's
wake last night.

12:53.573 --> 12:56.407
God only knows how many are
gonna be at the funeral today.

12:56.493 --> 12:59.778
You really think a grand jury's
just gonna ignore all that?

12:59.880 --> 13:03.765
♪♪

13:03.800 --> 13:05.817
you already talk like
you got it in the bag.

13:05.902 --> 13:07.685
The law is the law.

13:07.788 --> 13:09.420
Just trying to do
my job.

13:11.741 --> 13:13.424
Look, if sheriff strider
really is getting threats,

13:13.527 --> 13:15.193
they aren't coming
from us.

13:15.278 --> 13:17.962
There's probably some
well-intentioned white person

13:18.048 --> 13:19.264
who thinks they're helping
the cause.

13:19.366 --> 13:21.499
Or ill-intentioned,
trying to stir up some mess.

13:21.585 --> 13:23.034
Packton: I hate to be the one
to break it to you,

13:23.103 --> 13:25.170
but a bunch of us staying
out at the delta inn

13:25.238 --> 13:28.006
saw those threatening letters,
and they didn't look doctored.

13:28.074 --> 13:29.507
Huh.

13:29.576 --> 13:30.692
Well, that explains
how strider's threats

13:30.777 --> 13:32.159
ended up
in southern papers.

13:32.179 --> 13:33.812
Maybe we should invite him
out to dr. Howard's

13:33.897 --> 13:35.780
and see if he wants to set up
a follow-up interview.

13:35.866 --> 13:37.131
[ laughter ]

13:37.167 --> 13:38.650
y'all are staying out
at dr. Howard's,

13:38.768 --> 13:39.651
in mound bayou?

13:39.769 --> 13:41.085
We don't have
much choice.

13:41.171 --> 13:43.054
All the hotels in sumner
are whites only,

13:43.156 --> 13:44.739
and the few places
in clarksdale

13:44.791 --> 13:48.560
that will accommodate us
are fully booked.

13:48.645 --> 13:51.112
I reckon dr. Howard's is
finer than any hotel

13:51.214 --> 13:53.180
I ever set foot in.

13:53.283 --> 13:55.633
I reckon you're right.

13:55.735 --> 13:59.137
So, you were in chicago
last night, for the viewing?

13:59.206 --> 14:00.171
I was.

14:00.257 --> 14:01.756
I-I haven't seen
any of the footage.

14:01.808 --> 14:04.742
Is it as bad as they're saying?
His face?

14:06.012 --> 14:06.994
It's worse.

14:07.097 --> 14:08.379
Reporter:
Sheriff strider.

14:08.465 --> 14:09.848
Would you care to comment
on the condition

14:09.966 --> 14:11.165
of the body
when you last saw it?

14:11.268 --> 14:13.000
Is it true that no autopsy
was performed?

14:13.103 --> 14:14.302
How about
the public viewing

14:14.387 --> 14:15.854
and the national media attention
this case is getting?

14:15.972 --> 14:17.171
When were you made aware
that emmett till's body

14:17.274 --> 14:18.606
wasn't buried
in mississippi?

14:18.692 --> 14:22.060
This whole thing is a farce!

14:22.145 --> 14:25.230
It is a hoax cooked up
by the naacp!

14:25.315 --> 14:26.981
You have something
against the naacp, sir?

14:27.067 --> 14:28.683
A hoax?

14:28.785 --> 14:30.985
Sheriff,
you were there

14:31.071 --> 14:33.371
when they pulled that boy
from the river.

14:33.490 --> 14:37.825
♪♪

14:37.911 --> 14:40.245
I seen the paper.

14:40.330 --> 14:42.080
The photo of that boy
when he's "alive"

14:42.165 --> 14:44.966
don't look like
nothing I saw.

14:45.051 --> 14:47.502
I was trusting the word
of the uncle.

14:47.587 --> 14:49.754
Maybe that's where
I went wrong.

14:49.839 --> 14:53.591
But as far as I know,
that boy's still alive.

14:53.677 --> 14:55.977
[ crowd murmuring ]

14:56.062 --> 14:58.479
[ door opens, closes ]

15:01.150 --> 15:02.617
I don't understand.

15:02.719 --> 15:04.319
That man signed
emmett's death certificate.

15:04.421 --> 15:05.570
How can he call this
a hoax?

15:05.655 --> 15:07.572
He's using the press
to sway the grand jury.

15:07.657 --> 15:09.657
In his own county?

15:09.726 --> 15:11.426
What kind of people
are these?

15:11.494 --> 15:13.895
The kind looking to preserve
their way of life

15:13.964 --> 15:15.947
by any means necessary.

15:15.999 --> 15:17.332
He wouldn't pull a move
like this

15:17.384 --> 15:20.618
unless he thought we had a real
shot at getting an indictment.

15:20.654 --> 15:23.137
So I say we beat him
at his own game

15:23.206 --> 15:25.640
and use the press
to call his bluff.

15:27.928 --> 15:30.311
We're supposed to bury
emmett tomorrow.

15:32.749 --> 15:35.767
But I'm willing to delay it.

15:35.802 --> 15:37.752
Thousands of people
are waiting to see my boy,

15:37.821 --> 15:40.455
and this will
give them more time.

15:40.523 --> 15:42.690
If that sheriff doesn't think
it's emmett,

15:42.792 --> 15:45.460
let him come up here
and see for himself.

15:45.562 --> 15:48.513
♪♪

15:48.598 --> 15:52.266
the sheriff and the d.A.
Are supposed to be partners.

15:52.352 --> 15:53.935
Instead,
clarence blindsides me

15:54.020 --> 15:56.571
the weekend before
my grand jury hearing.

15:56.690 --> 15:58.906
So now not only am I gonna
have to connect

15:59.025 --> 16:01.743
bryant and milam's kidnapping
confession to till's murder

16:01.861 --> 16:05.246
to get the indictment,
I gotta convince the jury

16:05.365 --> 16:08.916
that the boy's body
really is the boy's body.

16:09.035 --> 16:12.203
Clarence has about as much couth
as a timber rattlesnake.

16:12.288 --> 16:14.922
I ain't a bit surprised
by what he did.

16:15.925 --> 16:17.375
Did that photo
of the cotton gin fan

16:17.460 --> 16:19.293
lead to anyone coming
forward with information?

16:19.379 --> 16:20.294
Not yet.

16:20.380 --> 16:23.131
What about
the third man?

16:23.216 --> 16:26.384
The colored man mose wright saw
at his house that night

16:26.469 --> 16:27.802
with bryant and milam?

16:27.887 --> 16:32.223
Until we have a name, all we can
do is keep asking questions.

16:32.308 --> 16:33.891
So that's it, huh?

16:33.977 --> 16:37.111
Until you have a name,
I'm dead in the water.

16:37.230 --> 16:39.063
I didn't say that.

16:43.236 --> 16:44.452
There's some talk
going around

16:44.571 --> 16:46.621
that a second colored man
may have been involved.

16:46.740 --> 16:48.373
Is that right?

16:48.458 --> 16:51.542
We don't have anything solid
yet -- on either witness --

16:51.628 --> 16:54.078
but these rumors
mean something.

16:54.164 --> 16:55.246
People around here
wouldn't be talking

16:55.331 --> 16:56.964
unless folks
were scared,

16:57.083 --> 16:59.801
and they're scared
'cause we're close.

16:59.919 --> 17:02.420
Yeah,
just not close enough.

17:02.505 --> 17:04.422
We ain't
giving up.

17:04.507 --> 17:07.675
Me and my deputies are hell-bent
on finding these guys.

17:09.729 --> 17:11.179
By chance, you think
you can find 'em

17:11.264 --> 17:13.848
before I face the grand jury
in the morning?

17:15.935 --> 17:18.603
Chatham:
Deputy cothran, you took
mose wright's initial statement

17:18.688 --> 17:19.970
that emmett till was missing.

17:20.073 --> 17:20.988
Is that right?

17:21.107 --> 17:22.407
Deputy cothran:
Yes, sir, I did.

17:22.492 --> 17:24.809
And you were on the scene
when the body was identified?

17:24.911 --> 17:26.977
Yes.
And who identified
the body?

17:27.080 --> 17:28.246
Mose wright.

17:28.331 --> 17:30.448
Given the condition
of the body,

17:30.533 --> 17:32.817
was mose wright able
to ascertain,

17:32.919 --> 17:34.318
to your satisfaction,

17:34.421 --> 17:37.004
the identity of his
great-nephew emmett till?

17:37.123 --> 17:38.005
Yes.

17:38.124 --> 17:39.824
Mose said it was the boy.

17:39.926 --> 17:41.209
He was sure of it.

17:41.294 --> 17:45.012
Even in its terrible condition.

17:45.131 --> 17:49.667
And then there was the boy's
ring that backed it up.

17:49.769 --> 17:51.335
What kind of ring
was it?

17:51.438 --> 17:52.553
It was silver.

17:52.639 --> 17:55.857
And an inscription,
the initials l.T.

17:55.975 --> 17:57.642
And what did you do
with that ring

17:57.727 --> 17:59.644
after you removed it
from the body?

17:59.729 --> 18:01.312
I gave it to
mose wright.

18:01.397 --> 18:03.865
Chester, tell me,
were you able to determine

18:03.983 --> 18:06.851
the race of the body
by looking at it?

18:06.953 --> 18:10.521
Yes, sir,
it was a negro.

18:10.623 --> 18:13.791
Is there any doubt in your mind
that the body retrieved

18:13.877 --> 18:18.329
from the tallahatchie river
on August 31st was emmett till?

18:18.414 --> 18:20.882
Based upon the information
I was given, no.

18:21.000 --> 18:22.216
No doubt in my mind.

18:22.318 --> 18:24.802
After deputy cothran relayed
mose wright's statement,

18:24.888 --> 18:27.171
that a man identifying himself
as mr. Bryant

18:27.257 --> 18:29.257
abducted emmett till
from his home,

18:29.342 --> 18:30.925
did you pay roy bryant
a visit?

18:31.010 --> 18:33.661
Yes.
Did you ask him if mose wright's
statement was true?

18:33.746 --> 18:35.129
I did.
And what did he say?

18:35.198 --> 18:38.149
That he kidnapped the boy,
just like mose wright said.

18:38.201 --> 18:41.018
And what did you do after
roy bryant confessed?

18:41.070 --> 18:43.320
I arrested him.

18:43.373 --> 18:44.806
Tell us
what you did next.

18:44.891 --> 18:46.707
I did a brief examination
of the body.

18:46.810 --> 18:49.010
Did you perform
an autopsy?
No.

18:49.095 --> 18:52.730
It was more of a postmortem,
given the severe decomposition.

18:52.782 --> 18:54.982
During the exam,
were you able to determine

18:55.051 --> 18:56.634
the race of the body?

18:56.719 --> 18:59.003
No. Not with
complete certainty.

19:08.882 --> 19:10.932
You were present when
chester miller

19:11.034 --> 19:15.236
took possession of the body,
were you not?

19:15.305 --> 19:16.470
I was.

19:16.556 --> 19:18.606
One can only assume
a negro undertaker is called

19:18.725 --> 19:20.691
when a negro victim
is involved.

19:20.743 --> 19:22.727
Would that
be accurate?

19:22.779 --> 19:25.463
In normal circumstances,
when the victim's race

19:25.498 --> 19:28.132
is immediately
identifiable, yes,

19:28.184 --> 19:29.684
but it wasn't.

19:29.752 --> 19:31.652
And<i> I</i> didn't make the call
to the undertaker.

19:35.208 --> 19:40.778
Do you believe that body
to be one of a negro, dr. Otken?

19:40.830 --> 19:42.230
♪♪

19:42.332 --> 19:44.799
I can't say
for sure.

19:44.884 --> 19:46.417
What I<i> can</i> say,
with certainty,

19:46.502 --> 19:48.870
is that emmett till
was missing for three days

19:48.938 --> 19:50.771
when the body was retrieved
from the river.

19:50.840 --> 19:52.790
That extreme level
of decomposition

19:52.825 --> 19:55.476
after such a short amount
of time in the water

19:55.578 --> 19:57.612
is highly unlikely.

19:57.697 --> 20:00.631
Therefore, I can only conclude
that the body in question

20:00.683 --> 20:02.516
is not that
of emmett till.

20:02.585 --> 20:08.138
♪♪

20:08.241 --> 20:17.231
♪♪

20:17.333 --> 20:19.984
[ shovel thuds ]

20:26.459 --> 20:28.659
it's over.

20:28.745 --> 20:30.211
I gave them two days
to come up here

20:30.330 --> 20:31.662
and examine
emmett's body,

20:31.748 --> 20:34.916
and if they really had any
doubts, they would've come.

20:35.001 --> 20:36.334
I suppose
I should be grateful

20:36.419 --> 20:38.386
that we even got a hearing
in the first place.

20:38.504 --> 20:41.038
It was greedy of me
to expect more.

20:41.140 --> 20:43.707
Nonsense.

20:43.810 --> 20:47.228
Baby, you got to give yourself
a break from the case.

20:48.815 --> 20:51.565
You're right.

20:51.684 --> 20:55.603
What happens next
is out of my hands.

20:55.688 --> 20:57.321
And I'll drive myself mad
wondering

20:57.407 --> 20:59.357
what the grand jury's
gonna do

20:59.442 --> 21:01.909
when history
has already shown me.

21:03.279 --> 21:10.284
♪♪

21:10.370 --> 21:17.408
♪♪

21:17.510 --> 21:18.676
[ radio clicks ]

21:18.761 --> 21:20.878
<i> after tens of thousands</i>
<i> of people</i>

21:20.964 --> 21:22.930
<i> filed past his casket</i>
<i> over the weekend,</i>

21:23.049 --> 21:25.749
<i> emmett till was finally</i>
<i> laid to rest this morning</i>

21:25.852 --> 21:26.851
<i> at burr oak cemetery.</i>

21:26.936 --> 21:29.103
[ radio tuning ]

21:29.222 --> 21:32.023
<i> this is for all you</i>
<i> lovebirds out there,</i>

21:32.108 --> 21:35.443
<i> here's the platters' smash hit</i>
<i> "only you."</i>

21:35.561 --> 21:39.981
♪♪

21:40.066 --> 21:45.486
♪<i> only you</i> ♪

21:45.588 --> 21:52.059
♪<i> can make all this world</i>
<i> seem right</i> ♪

21:52.161 --> 21:57.581
♪<i> only you</i> ♪

21:57.667 --> 22:04.055
♪ can make
the darkness bright ♪

22:04.140 --> 22:10.961
♪ only you and you alone ♪

22:11.064 --> 22:12.796
♪ can thrill me ♪

22:12.899 --> 22:17.318
[ phone ringing ]
♪<i> like you do</i> ♪

22:17.437 --> 22:20.855
♪<i> my one and only...</i> ♪

22:20.940 --> 22:22.990
hello?

22:23.092 --> 22:25.943
Yes, rayfield.

22:26.029 --> 22:28.496
No, no one's
called me yet.

22:28.598 --> 22:34.785
♪ can make
all this change in me ♪

22:34.871 --> 22:38.539
we, the jury, find that
roy bryant and j.W. Milam

22:38.624 --> 22:42.159
did willfully,
unlawfully, feloniously,

22:42.261 --> 22:47.048
and of their malice aforethought
kill and murder emmett till,

22:47.133 --> 22:48.832
a human being.

22:48.935 --> 22:50.684
I can't believe it.

22:50.803 --> 22:52.853
There's gonna be
a trial.

22:52.955 --> 22:54.021
I have to call mama.

22:54.140 --> 23:00.144
♪ understand the magic
that you do ♪

23:00.229 --> 23:04.532
♪ you're my dream come true ♪

23:04.650 --> 23:09.153
♪ my one and only ♪

23:09.238 --> 23:11.038
♪ you ♪

23:11.140 --> 23:22.199
♪ one and only you ♪

23:22.285 --> 23:23.617
we have to thank you,
rayfield,

23:23.736 --> 23:26.770
for introducing us
to everyone at the naacp --

23:26.856 --> 23:28.155
we're forever grateful.

23:28.241 --> 23:29.740
No need to thank me.

23:29.826 --> 23:31.775
The credit belongs
to mamie.

23:31.878 --> 23:33.043
I don't have to
tell y'all,

23:33.129 --> 23:35.963
this indictment
is unprecedented.

23:36.032 --> 23:37.765
You know, before the viewing,
I was afraid

23:37.834 --> 23:41.702
that I was making a mistake
letting the public in.

23:41.737 --> 23:43.804
And then, right around the time
I started hearing people

23:43.890 --> 23:45.573
screaming at
the sight of my boy

23:45.658 --> 23:50.678
like he was some sort of monster
at a horror picture,

23:50.746 --> 23:54.264
I was tempted
to shut that casket,

23:54.317 --> 23:57.334
and I'm so glad
that I didn't.

23:57.386 --> 23:59.987
Now I know that it had to be
done to get us here.

24:00.106 --> 24:03.941
Amen.
You made this happen.

24:03.976 --> 24:06.927
And you can<i> keep</i>
making things happen.

24:07.013 --> 24:09.330
Mr. Wilkins is
keeping his word.

24:09.398 --> 24:11.932
The naacp would like you
to speak at a rally

24:12.001 --> 24:14.251
at st. Matthew's methodist
on the 16th.

24:14.353 --> 24:15.369
Alma: I'm sorry.

24:15.455 --> 24:17.171
They want mamie to speak?
For what reason?

24:17.256 --> 24:18.639
To continue the work --

24:18.708 --> 24:21.826
to keep telling people
to fight on behalf of emmett --

24:21.878 --> 24:24.512
because these cases are
rarely won in the courtroom.

24:24.614 --> 24:25.713
Gene: He's right.

24:25.781 --> 24:27.515
The more
we talk about emmett --

24:27.600 --> 24:31.068
who he was,
who he could've been --

24:31.154 --> 24:33.487
the better chance we have
at a conviction.

24:33.556 --> 24:37.258
Mamie has given a couple of
statements to local reporters.

24:37.343 --> 24:39.143
Now you want her to
get on stage,

24:39.228 --> 24:41.111
at a political rally
of all things?

24:41.164 --> 24:42.213
She's a mother.

24:42.248 --> 24:43.898
Making speeches
is not her job.

24:43.983 --> 24:48.135
I think what mama is saying is
we could use a little privacy,

24:48.204 --> 24:50.387
and me getting up on a stage,
well, that --

24:50.439 --> 24:52.039
that's not gonna get us any.

24:52.141 --> 24:54.058
[ sighs ]

24:54.143 --> 24:56.460
what's done is done,
mamie.

24:56.496 --> 24:59.230
You're all over the papers
and on television.

24:59.265 --> 25:02.967
Now you have to decide
if all your hard work

25:03.019 --> 25:06.654
was only about
emmett...

25:06.722 --> 25:09.356
Or about all of us.

25:09.442 --> 25:12.259
Unless the naacp keeps
pressuring states

25:12.345 --> 25:13.677
like mississippi,

25:13.763 --> 25:17.364
real citizenship for the negro
will always be elusive.

25:17.433 --> 25:19.433
If the government can't make
mississippi change,

25:19.502 --> 25:21.151
what makes you think
the naacp can?

25:21.237 --> 25:22.586
I don't care how much
pressure you apply.

25:22.622 --> 25:24.438
How are my friends
from the north?

25:24.524 --> 25:26.891
Booker: Dr. Howard.
Great to see you.

25:26.976 --> 25:29.159
Helen tells me you settled
in the guest house just fine.

25:29.245 --> 25:30.511
Oh, better than fine.
Thank you.

25:30.563 --> 25:31.628
Join us.

25:31.731 --> 25:32.729
We were just
disagreeing about

25:32.782 --> 25:34.498
the future
of mississippi negroes.

25:34.584 --> 25:37.501
I see. A little light
conversation over lunch, huh?

25:37.603 --> 25:38.702
Jimmy here thinks that

25:38.738 --> 25:39.770
if the u.S. Government

25:39.822 --> 25:41.355
can't enforce integration
down here,

25:41.424 --> 25:43.574
negroes won't
be able to either.

25:43.609 --> 25:46.160
Now, I think the naacp can force
the state's hand.

25:46.262 --> 25:47.294
Well, don't count out

25:47.380 --> 25:49.296
the regional negro
leadership council.

25:49.365 --> 25:51.715
Ever since we organized
the gas station boycott,

25:51.751 --> 25:54.885
there are negro restrooms
in every station in mississippi.

25:54.937 --> 25:57.538
With all due respect,
a gas station boycott,

25:57.640 --> 25:59.122
as powerful
as it was,

25:59.175 --> 26:02.610
wasn't a declaration of war
on white folks' way of life.

26:02.678 --> 26:04.511
I'm on a hit-list of
the most powerful

26:04.614 --> 26:06.947
white supremacist organization
in the south.

26:07.016 --> 26:10.985
So, with all due respect,
I beg to differ.

26:12.538 --> 26:14.305
The white citizens' council
considers

26:14.357 --> 26:16.874
<i> any</i> attempt at integration
an act of war,

26:16.909 --> 26:19.426
be it learning,
using the restrooms, voting --

26:19.495 --> 26:22.796
and they are far more powerful
than the klan,

26:22.898 --> 26:26.016
because they wear suits,
not hoods.

26:26.068 --> 26:28.636
They're doctors, they're judges,
they're lawyers,

26:28.738 --> 26:30.187
and they are responsible
for killing

26:30.222 --> 26:33.257
two of my closest friends
this year.

26:33.292 --> 26:35.843
We may have a long way to go
with smith and lee's cases,

26:35.911 --> 26:37.845
but the till trial,

26:37.913 --> 26:40.447
that's proof we're only going to
take so much down here.

26:40.549 --> 26:41.749
Maybe.

26:41.817 --> 26:42.967
But what if
they plead guilty

26:43.002 --> 26:45.135
to avoid a trial --
and the death penalty?

26:45.187 --> 26:47.721
I mean, bryant did confess
to kidnapping the boy.

26:47.807 --> 26:50.024
He also said
he let him go.

26:50.092 --> 26:51.642
We all know that they didn't,
but why else

26:51.694 --> 26:52.793
would the sheriff
run with this theory

26:52.862 --> 26:54.244
that the body
isn't emmett's?

26:54.297 --> 26:56.330
To cast doubt on the jury pool.

26:56.415 --> 26:57.898
There isn't a negro
registered to vote

26:57.967 --> 27:00.367
in this entire county,
thanks to the citizens' council.

27:00.453 --> 27:03.453
If we can't vote,
we can't be jurors.

27:03.506 --> 27:05.973
No one in that
deliberation room

27:06.042 --> 27:07.241
is going to look
like emmett.

27:07.326 --> 27:08.559
Or his mother.

27:08.594 --> 27:10.544
Well, that's why we're not
leaving it to the lawyers

27:10.579 --> 27:13.681
or whatever jury they scrounge
up to ensure a conviction.

27:13.766 --> 27:17.851
It is up to us to make sure
that this is a fair trial.

27:17.937 --> 27:19.753
How the hell we gonna
stack the jury

27:19.822 --> 27:21.338
when everybody
in tallahatchie county

27:21.424 --> 27:22.339
knows good and well

27:22.391 --> 27:24.558
bryant and milam are
redneck peckerwoods?

27:24.627 --> 27:29.113
Well, I guess we'll have to bus
jurors in from hinds county.

27:29.165 --> 27:30.798
Jesse, didn't your firm
sue milam

27:30.916 --> 27:32.032
a couple times
for bootlegging?

27:32.101 --> 27:34.835
A couple?
Too many times to count.

27:34.937 --> 27:36.804
Be that as it may,
those boys are gonna be tried

27:36.872 --> 27:39.239
by a jury of good, white,
anglo-saxon men,

27:39.325 --> 27:43.694
and I assure you we will find
12 suitable men for the job.

27:43.779 --> 27:45.245
What about
bryant's wife?

27:45.314 --> 27:47.848
She's just as southern as they
come, and that's good for us.

27:47.917 --> 27:48.982
You're not thinking
about putting her

27:49.051 --> 27:51.318
on the stand,
are you?

27:51.387 --> 27:52.453
It's too risky.

27:52.521 --> 27:53.854
We need a joinder.

27:53.923 --> 27:56.306
If we try bryant and milam
as co-defendants,

27:56.342 --> 27:57.691
the state can't
ask carolyn

27:57.760 --> 27:59.360
to testify against
her own husband.

27:59.462 --> 28:04.114
Hold on.
Let's talk about this.

28:04.166 --> 28:07.101
Don't we want her
to testify?

28:07.186 --> 28:09.937
Well, I don't see
how that benefits us.

28:10.039 --> 28:12.072
The wolf whistle, that's why.

28:12.141 --> 28:14.708
If she can't testify, how do we
bring it into evidence?

28:14.794 --> 28:16.944
Well,
call me simple,

28:17.029 --> 28:19.196
but doesn't the whistle
give the state motive?

28:19.248 --> 28:21.148
[ chuckles ]

28:21.250 --> 28:22.816
maybe.

28:25.287 --> 28:27.788
Maybe that's okay.

28:27.823 --> 28:30.657
Judge swango:
You men are here today to enter
a plea on the charge of murder.

28:30.726 --> 28:31.658
What say you?

28:31.744 --> 28:33.060
Not guilty,
your honor.

28:33.129 --> 28:35.396
And you, mr. Bryant?

28:35.498 --> 28:40.868
♪♪

28:40.953 --> 28:43.420
not guilty.

28:43.472 --> 28:45.873
Behind me, you'll find the
best group of trial attorneys

28:45.991 --> 28:47.624
in all of
tallahatchie county,

28:47.676 --> 28:49.093
and we are extremely confident

28:49.178 --> 28:50.477
that we have more than
enough proof

28:50.546 --> 28:54.515
that the body found in the river
wasn't that of emmett till.

28:54.583 --> 28:56.834
[ crowd murmuring ]

28:56.886 --> 28:58.302
not only do we believe
the state

28:58.337 --> 29:00.154
will be unable to prove
this essential fact,

29:00.239 --> 29:02.456
we believe that the proof
for the defendants

29:02.541 --> 29:04.191
will convince
any reasonable person

29:04.260 --> 29:07.811
that in all probability,
the body was that of a dead man

29:07.847 --> 29:09.980
transported from some other
section to this county

29:10.032 --> 29:13.150
by activists trying to stir up
racial tensions.

29:13.185 --> 29:14.852
If you don't believe that's
the body of emmett till,

29:14.937 --> 29:16.120
then who is it?

29:16.205 --> 29:17.104
Where did it
come from?

29:17.206 --> 29:19.189
The investigation is ongoing.

29:19.225 --> 29:20.607
What about
the boy's mother?

29:20.676 --> 29:22.643
How could you possibly think
she'd be involved in a "hoax"?

29:22.728 --> 29:24.361
Well, you know,
I don't pretend to understand

29:24.396 --> 29:26.830
what goes on
in the minds of you people.

29:26.882 --> 29:30.100
Uh, we'll save that discussion
for the witness stand.

29:30.186 --> 29:31.618
Now,
our team has learned

29:31.704 --> 29:34.621
that the d.A. Intends
to invite mamie down here

29:34.690 --> 29:38.358
to challenge our theory,
and we welcome that fight.

29:38.427 --> 29:39.760
Our only hope

29:39.845 --> 29:42.996
is that she does not invite
trouble along the way.

29:43.065 --> 29:45.365
In mississippi, jurors don't
take too kindly

29:45.434 --> 29:47.117
to outside agitators.

29:47.169 --> 29:48.118
That'll be all.

29:48.204 --> 29:49.803
Thank you.

29:52.158 --> 29:56.059
Hicks:
Ruby hurley and medgar evers.

29:56.111 --> 29:57.978
I thought I saw breland
wet himself.

29:58.063 --> 29:59.413
Now I know why.

29:59.482 --> 30:01.598
It's the naacp's
dynamic duo.

30:01.684 --> 30:04.451
[ chuckles ]

30:04.570 --> 30:06.203
I take it
you both just got in?

30:06.288 --> 30:08.505
We just drove up
from belzoni.

30:08.591 --> 30:11.408
You two are always
burning the midnight oil.

30:11.510 --> 30:12.843
How's reverend lee's case
coming along?

30:12.928 --> 30:14.378
Look at you, always digging.

30:14.463 --> 30:15.712
Are you ever off the clock?

30:15.798 --> 30:17.548
That's rich,
coming from you.

30:17.633 --> 30:18.932
Tell me,
what's the word?

30:19.051 --> 30:20.300
Any chance
for an indictment?

30:20.386 --> 30:22.586
When we have something
concrete to share,

30:22.688 --> 30:24.438
you'll be
the first to know, jimmy.

30:24.557 --> 30:26.306
Right after the fbi.

30:26.392 --> 30:28.091
Alright, you two.

30:28.194 --> 30:29.693
We're heading over
to dr howard's.

30:29.778 --> 30:31.111
Can we give you
a lift?

30:31.230 --> 30:34.598
No, I think I'm gonna poke
around here a little longer.

30:34.700 --> 30:36.366
I'll see you out there later.

30:36.452 --> 30:38.068
Alright.

30:43.375 --> 30:45.942
[ engine starts ]

30:46.045 --> 30:48.328
[ vehicle departs ]

30:48.414 --> 30:52.165
♪♪

30:52.251 --> 30:53.967
man:
You a reporter?

30:55.804 --> 30:57.954
You heard about
that third man?

30:58.057 --> 30:59.339
Who hasn't?

30:59.408 --> 31:01.525
The police have been trying
to track him down for days.

31:01.610 --> 31:03.093
That surprise you?

31:03.128 --> 31:04.728
Not at all.

31:04.763 --> 31:06.079
If I knew something,
the sheriff's office

31:06.165 --> 31:08.465
is the last place
I'd go with it.

31:11.086 --> 31:12.336
What do you know?

31:12.371 --> 31:14.221
His name.

31:14.290 --> 31:15.989
Goes by too tight.

31:16.041 --> 31:19.259
He's got a friend tending bar
over at kings in glendora.

31:19.345 --> 31:21.495
From what I hear,
she might talk,

31:21.564 --> 31:23.597
just not to the law --
or anybody in the press.

31:25.634 --> 31:28.385
Mamie: "let the death of my son
light a fire in you

31:28.437 --> 31:32.706
so powerful that hatred
cannot extinguish it."

31:32.775 --> 31:34.908
[ sighs ] good lord.

31:34.977 --> 31:37.811
[ phone ringing ]

31:42.501 --> 31:44.685
hello?

31:44.770 --> 31:45.736
Hello?

31:45.771 --> 31:47.371
Woman:
<i> Mamie bradley?</i>

31:47.423 --> 31:48.722
Yes.

31:48.824 --> 31:52.042
<i>You thinking about going down</i>
<i>to mississippi to testify?</i>

31:52.127 --> 31:53.226
Who is this?

31:53.329 --> 31:54.761
<i> You go ahead.</i>

31:54.830 --> 31:55.963
<i> When you come back</i>
<i> to chicago,</i>

31:56.031 --> 31:58.265
<i>we've got a bomb ready</i>
<i>for you and mayor daley.</i>

31:58.367 --> 32:00.534
[ click ]

32:04.221 --> 32:06.073
they're threatening to kill her
if she goes down there,

32:06.141 --> 32:07.741
and you still want her
to testify?

32:07.810 --> 32:10.210
Jury selection begins
in three days.

32:10.279 --> 32:12.679
You tell me what mamie
can say to the jury

32:12.748 --> 32:15.248
that mose
and the police can't.

32:15.284 --> 32:18.452
They never called mose
to testify for the grand jury,

32:18.520 --> 32:20.454
and they may not call him
for the trial either.

32:20.556 --> 32:22.489
Why not?
Who could say?

32:22.558 --> 32:24.758
What matters is we got
the indictment.

32:24.860 --> 32:26.727
And that district attorney
wouldn't call you down there

32:26.795 --> 32:28.629
unless he thought
it would help with his case.

32:28.664 --> 32:31.381
The defense is running
with strider's hoax theory.

32:31.400 --> 32:34.418
As crazy as it is,
it's carrying weight down there,

32:34.470 --> 32:36.303
but a mother's testimony
means something

32:36.388 --> 32:38.105
in a southern courtroom.

32:40.776 --> 32:43.543
Mamie...

32:43.662 --> 32:45.812
What do<i> you</i>
want to do?

32:45.898 --> 32:48.682
I don't know.

32:48.751 --> 32:50.600
But if I went,
I couldn't go alone...

32:50.686 --> 32:51.752
I'll close down
the barbershop.

32:51.870 --> 32:52.719
I'll come with you.

32:52.821 --> 32:53.937
Oh, I can't
let you do that.

32:53.973 --> 32:55.622
Then we'd be without
two incomes.

32:55.708 --> 32:56.740
Then I'll escort you.

32:56.792 --> 32:59.426
And I can take a leave
from work, honey.

32:59.461 --> 33:01.928
Do you think the state would
provide protection for us?

33:02.031 --> 33:04.047
Our friends at the naacp
sent a telegram

33:04.133 --> 33:06.733
to mississippi
requesting state protection.

33:06.802 --> 33:09.219
We haven't heard back --
but I can assure you

33:09.271 --> 33:10.821
that you'll be under
the full protection

33:10.873 --> 33:12.172
of one of the finest,

33:12.257 --> 33:14.825
most influential leaders
in mississippi,

33:14.877 --> 33:17.928
dr. Theodore roosevelt howard.

33:18.013 --> 33:19.479
Oh, you're familiar.

33:19.565 --> 33:21.648
Of course.
I read the papers.

33:21.717 --> 33:23.750
No one's fought harder
for our rights down there.

33:23.819 --> 33:25.352
And he wants to
help me?

33:25.421 --> 33:27.888
Well, he'd be honored to house
you during the trial.

33:27.956 --> 33:29.723
To put your mind at ease,

33:29.792 --> 33:32.492
his home comes with
a live-in security team.

33:32.578 --> 33:34.294
Yeah, we're talking
about armed guards.

33:34.363 --> 33:35.762
Armed guards?

33:35.864 --> 33:39.733
Mamie, you have already
given so much.

33:39.802 --> 33:41.635
Now is not the time
for you to be

33:41.704 --> 33:44.421
making speeches and
causing trouble --

33:44.473 --> 33:47.140
not when
your life is on the line.

33:50.379 --> 33:54.514
♪♪

33:54.633 --> 33:57.017
according to
this paper,

33:57.086 --> 33:59.820
bryant and milam,
they are war heroes

33:59.888 --> 34:01.822
who "never got into
any meanness."

34:01.890 --> 34:04.608
and that woman, the wife?

34:04.660 --> 34:06.927
"a pretty brunette."

34:07.012 --> 34:09.129
they're calling me
an outside agitator, mama --

34:09.198 --> 34:11.915
me, the mother
of a murdered child.

34:11.967 --> 34:13.249
Mama,
if I stay up here

34:13.302 --> 34:15.452
and I curl up in some ball
and hide,

34:15.487 --> 34:18.638
then I<i> am</i> an outsider,
an occasional<i> agitator</i>

34:18.724 --> 34:21.158
when it's convenient for me
to speak up.

34:21.210 --> 34:23.259
When it's self-serving.

34:23.312 --> 34:26.379
But if I go and I give
that speech tomorrow

34:26.498 --> 34:27.664
and I show up
at that courtroom

34:27.750 --> 34:30.417
and I tell the jury
what only I can say --

34:30.486 --> 34:33.169
is that it was my boy
in that box --

34:33.222 --> 34:35.572
then maybe it will show them
that my -- my --

34:35.624 --> 34:38.341
my words aren't meant
to cause trouble.

34:38.393 --> 34:41.995
That this isn't some kind
of political statement.

34:42.081 --> 34:44.614
[ voice breaking ]
this is pain.

34:44.650 --> 34:46.716
It's a mother grieving
for her child.

34:46.752 --> 34:48.602
They already done took
my only grandson,

34:48.687 --> 34:50.820
and I'm not gonna
let them take you, too!

34:50.873 --> 34:54.357
I know
this is hard,

34:54.393 --> 34:57.327
because you raised me
to be a good girl,

34:57.379 --> 35:01.364
and good girls
don't fight back,

35:01.416 --> 35:04.785
but I can't help but wonder
where I would be

35:04.870 --> 35:08.688
if you had raised me
to fight.

35:08.807 --> 35:12.659
If we had all been
brought up to fight.

35:12.694 --> 35:14.995
I keep feeling like I'm watching
some other woman

35:15.063 --> 35:17.931
talk to reporters
and calling the shots,

35:18.016 --> 35:21.401
because before emmett was gone,
mama, that was your job,

35:21.503 --> 35:22.969
and I let you do it --

35:23.055 --> 35:25.122
all the heavy lifting
and the fighting.

35:25.157 --> 35:28.208
But, mama...

35:28.310 --> 35:30.911
It's my turn.

35:30.979 --> 35:33.763
I want to become
that brave woman,

35:33.866 --> 35:36.800
a woman like you,
mama.

35:36.835 --> 35:39.903
So maybe I can show someone
that one person --

35:39.955 --> 35:43.506
one mother --
can make a difference.

35:43.592 --> 35:48.128
♪♪

35:48.197 --> 35:49.896
if you want to invite danger
into your life,

35:49.965 --> 35:53.266
I can't stop you...

35:53.368 --> 35:54.801
But I won't have
any part of it.

35:54.903 --> 35:58.922
♪♪

35:58.974 --> 36:00.740
[ sighs ]

36:00.809 --> 36:05.094
♪♪

36:05.180 --> 36:09.783
[ applause ]

36:15.224 --> 36:17.474
thank you for that warm welcome.

36:20.612 --> 36:24.014
During the past few weeks,
I've spent a lot of time

36:24.049 --> 36:28.802
trying to find the right words
to get through each day.

36:28.871 --> 36:34.140
Nothing ever seems to fit,
because the truth is,

36:34.226 --> 36:38.011
nothing can ever prepare
a mother for losing her child.

36:44.386 --> 36:49.756
♪♪

36:49.825 --> 36:55.161
♪♪

36:55.247 --> 37:01.101
a month ago, I had a six-room
apartment here in chicago.

37:01.186 --> 37:04.471
I had a good job. I had a son.

37:04.539 --> 37:06.556
And when something happened
to negroes in the south,

37:06.642 --> 37:07.807
I said, "that's --

37:07.893 --> 37:10.744
that's their business,
not mine."

37:10.812 --> 37:13.046
now I know how wrong I was.

37:13.115 --> 37:14.881
Uh-huh.
Yes.

37:14.967 --> 37:17.934
The death of my son
has shown me

37:17.986 --> 37:21.805
that whatever happens to any
of us, anywhere in the world,

37:21.840 --> 37:24.574
had better be the business
of all of us.

37:24.626 --> 37:26.643
[ applause and exclamations ]

37:26.728 --> 37:32.715
♪♪

37:32.818 --> 37:38.855
♪♪

37:38.941 --> 37:51.735
♪♪

37:51.820 --> 37:55.705
♪ congratulations, honey ♪

37:55.791 --> 38:00.026
♪ if you found somebody new ♪

38:00.128 --> 38:02.162
♪ yeah ♪

38:02.247 --> 38:05.248
♪ congratulations, honey ♪

38:05.334 --> 38:08.835
♪ if you found somebody new ♪

38:08.920 --> 38:11.388
♪ yeah, oh, yeah ♪

38:11.473 --> 38:14.941
♪ I heard you found somebody ♪

38:15.043 --> 38:18.595
I'll take a beer,
whatever's cold.

38:18.680 --> 38:19.679
♪ yeah ♪

38:19.765 --> 38:21.348
sugar,
tell me somethin'.

38:21.433 --> 38:22.983
How is it that you're
in a juke joint

38:23.101 --> 38:24.484
and ain't got a stitch
of sweat on you?

38:24.603 --> 38:26.736
[ chuckles ]

38:26.822 --> 38:29.572
well, I guess I ain't got
no hips to shake.

38:29.658 --> 38:31.324
♪ yeah ♪

38:31.443 --> 38:33.860
I was actually hoping
to catch up with a friend.

38:33.945 --> 38:36.663
Goes by the name of
too tight.

38:36.782 --> 38:38.832
♪ yeah, oh, yeah ♪

38:38.950 --> 38:40.617
what you want
with him?

38:40.702 --> 38:42.369
Met him in the fields
a while back.

38:42.454 --> 38:43.953
He owes me a drink.

38:44.039 --> 38:45.038
How long's a while?

38:45.123 --> 38:46.456
A month or two.

38:46.541 --> 38:48.458
You ain't seen him
around much lately?

38:50.512 --> 38:53.013
Not in a spell.

38:53.131 --> 38:55.298
Guess we in
the same boat, then.

38:55.384 --> 38:56.516
How's that?

38:56.635 --> 38:58.668
I ain't seen him
since Monday.

38:58.770 --> 38:59.836
He's missing?

38:59.938 --> 39:01.971
He'd been staying with me
and my husband.

39:02.057 --> 39:04.340
They both work for one of them
milam brothers.

39:04.443 --> 39:06.443
♪ ...Found somebody new ♪

39:06.528 --> 39:09.112
listen, hon. I'd be happy
to help you find him.

39:09.197 --> 39:11.514
With your husband's help,
of course.

39:11.616 --> 39:13.116
How can I reach him?

39:13.201 --> 39:17.520
♪♪

39:17.622 --> 39:20.189
that's the problem.

39:20.292 --> 39:21.491
You can't.

39:24.379 --> 39:25.879
Henry lee's missing,
too.

39:25.997 --> 39:31.501
♪♪

39:31.586 --> 39:37.140
♪♪

39:37.175 --> 39:39.793
I hate this,

39:39.878 --> 39:42.529
but I couldn't let you go
down there being sore with me.

39:44.099 --> 39:48.151
The paper said you drew
quite a crowd at st matthew's.

39:48.186 --> 39:50.804
I couldn't see a single face
but gene's.

39:50.872 --> 39:53.306
You've always been
a fine speaker.

39:53.425 --> 39:55.809
I may not have raised you
to fight,

39:55.877 --> 39:57.844
but I guess I did something
right, didn't I?

39:57.946 --> 39:59.429
Mama.

39:59.531 --> 40:06.252
♪♪

40:06.338 --> 40:07.720
you be safe,
my girl.

40:07.806 --> 40:09.839
Daddy will
take good care of me.
[ sniffles ]

40:09.925 --> 40:11.374
don't you worry.

40:11.460 --> 40:14.978
♪♪

40:15.063 --> 40:16.713
I'll look in on
your mama.

40:16.748 --> 40:18.264
Thank you.

40:18.350 --> 40:25.789
♪♪

40:25.874 --> 40:27.340
go get 'em,
baby.

40:27.409 --> 40:35.932
♪♪

40:36.017 --> 40:38.401
[ airplane engine roars ]

40:38.453 --> 40:44.157
♪♪

40:44.276 --> 40:49.979
♪♪

40:50.081 --> 40:51.264
[ bell dings ]

40:51.383 --> 40:56.136
♪♪

40:56.254 --> 41:01.007
♪♪

41:01.109 --> 41:04.177
[ airplane engine roaring ]

41:04.246 --> 41:11.084
♪♪

41:11.186 --> 41:18.024
♪♪

41:18.126 --> 41:24.964
♪♪

41:25.066 --> 41:26.099
mamie: If you don't mind,

41:26.168 --> 41:28.101
I'd like to go
over the itinerary again --

41:28.170 --> 41:30.119
so daddy knows
what he's getting into.

41:30.172 --> 41:31.638
Rayfield: Of course.

41:31.723 --> 41:34.190
We've turned our itinerary
into our own version

41:34.292 --> 41:37.477
of the
underground railroad...

41:37.562 --> 41:39.295
Beginning with our arrival
in memphis,

41:39.331 --> 41:42.131
where we'll be driven
to our first safe house.

41:42.184 --> 41:48.555
♪♪

41:48.623 --> 41:51.257
welcome, mrs. Bradley.
Let's get you inside.

41:51.326 --> 41:53.543
After we cross, we'll make
our second stop

41:53.645 --> 41:55.278
at a safe house
in clarksdale,

41:55.330 --> 41:58.264
where we'll stay until it's safe
to continue into sumner.

41:58.350 --> 42:00.033
After the court recesses
for the day,

42:00.118 --> 42:02.719
we'll head out to mound bayou
to dr howard's,

42:02.754 --> 42:04.938
our safe house for
the duration of the trial.

42:05.023 --> 42:06.889
There have been reports
of mississippi troopers

42:06.992 --> 42:09.642
targeting out-of-towners
as they cross the state line.

42:09.711 --> 42:10.860
And I'm told they've gone
as far as

42:10.912 --> 42:13.680
to pass license plate numbers
on to the kkk.

42:13.765 --> 42:17.083
But if we sense any trouble,
we won't cross into mississippi.

42:17.185 --> 42:21.588
♪♪

42:21.673 --> 42:24.707
booker,
this is something else.

42:24.809 --> 42:27.093
I don't know how you kept
your composure in that room.

42:27.178 --> 42:29.312
I can't wait
to meet her.

42:29.397 --> 42:31.898
They sure do love her up north,
don't they?

42:32.017 --> 42:34.717
I hope she doesn't expect that
same warm welcome down here.

42:34.819 --> 42:36.319
Guard:
Stay back, stay back.

42:36.404 --> 42:37.820
Young man: Please, let me in.

42:37.906 --> 42:39.072
What's this about?

42:39.190 --> 42:42.191
It's about that chicago boy --
that boy that got killed!

42:45.080 --> 42:47.080
He needs to speak
to dr. Howard.

42:47.198 --> 42:49.449
It's urgent.

42:49.534 --> 42:51.367
[ knock on door ]

42:54.673 --> 42:56.456
what is it?

42:56.541 --> 43:01.160
On that morning, before those
men killed that boy,

43:01.229 --> 43:04.430
some field hands saw him riding
in the back of a pickup truck,

43:04.499 --> 43:06.583
sitting between
two negro men.

43:06.668 --> 43:07.734
Where?

43:07.802 --> 43:10.069
A plantation
out near drew.

43:10.171 --> 43:11.738
Near drew?

43:11.806 --> 43:13.456
Are you positive?
Yes, sir.

43:13.491 --> 43:15.475
There's more than one
field hand saying so.

43:15.560 --> 43:16.943
That's
sunflower county.

43:17.012 --> 43:18.694
Will your friends
talk to us?

43:18.747 --> 43:20.313
They ain't
my friends.

43:20.398 --> 43:21.514
I'm just telling you
what I heard.

43:21.549 --> 43:23.549
If we can head out to drew
and track them down,

43:23.635 --> 43:26.135
maybe we can tie bryant and
milam directly to the murder.

43:26.187 --> 43:29.055
If their stories
pan out,

43:29.140 --> 43:30.473
it means the trial's
in the wrong county.

43:30.525 --> 43:31.641
Which means we can
get it moved

43:31.693 --> 43:33.693
out of sheriff strider's
jurisdiction.

43:33.795 --> 43:35.128
Well, there's not
much time.

43:35.196 --> 43:37.563
Trial starts tomorrow.

43:37.632 --> 43:39.098
Then we better get started.

43:39.200 --> 43:45.188
♪♪

43:45.273 --> 43:47.190
this is it.

43:47.275 --> 43:48.908
Right up ahead.

43:49.027 --> 43:56.532
♪♪

43:56.618 --> 44:04.173
♪♪

44:04.259 --> 44:06.175
rayfield: Slow down.
It's a speed trap.

44:06.261 --> 44:07.927
Driver: No need
to tell me twice.

44:08.046 --> 44:12.131
♪♪

44:12.217 --> 44:13.749
all clear.

44:13.852 --> 44:16.803
♪♪

44:18.723 --> 44:21.357
♪♪

44:21.443 --> 44:23.693
[ gasps ]

44:23.778 --> 44:26.029
no.

44:26.114 --> 44:29.198
The state trooper's
following us.

44:29.284 --> 44:30.783
Dear god.

44:30.902 --> 44:36.772
♪♪

